[SN]TITLE[SN]
Several pilgrims hurt in Saudi coach crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Several Muslim pilgrims from Lancashire have been injured in a coach crash in Saudi Arabia.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Saudi driver of the coach, which was heading towards the city of Medina, died when the vehicle was in collision with a lorry.
The passengers, from East Lancashire, suffered cuts and bruises while a small number of people were taken to hospital for treatment.
The pilgrimage was organised by Blackburn-based Sadaat Travel.
